        <head xml:id="la30px-aaa238-Hd1e104">Proposition 1</head>
        <p xml:id="la30px-aaa238-d1e106">
          Proposition 1
        </p>
        <p xml:id="la30px-aaa238-d1e113">
          The Roman Pontiff is canonically elected Vicar of Jesus
          Christ and successor of Saint Peter. He has authority and power from Jesus Christ himself,
          Son of God, over all people in the world, whether of the Christian faithful or infidels,
          inasmuch as he may see fit in order to guide all people towards eternal life, and to
          remove impediments of eternal life. In one way he uses and should use this power with
          infidels, mostly those who never heard the Gospel, and in another way he uses it with the
          faithful or who were once faithful.
        </p>
      </div>
